Who: RODIMUS, Darkhawk, Perceptor
Location: Black Fortress - Security

Rodimus was busily running checks on the cell block system as Hydras
had Tuscon set inside the PIT. He looked admiringly at all the buttons
and controls, and how well everything fit together. He turned each
monitor on, and could see how easily he could switch from one cell to
another, and even view several at once should he choose. He could
control nearly every aspect of all the cells from here.

He could see from his monitor that Hydras was just having Tuscon put
in his cell so he turned up the sound . . .

> You look back at what you did wrong and you correct it. It's all right to make mistakes Rodimus, Primus knows I've made more than my fair share already."
>

"Yes you have made some mistakes today." Rodimus said over a speaker
near by Tuscon's ear, Rodimus chuckled at his own joke. "However you
will pay for it for a long long time."

(OOC: Sandy, I sent you an email also)

Rodimus was about to say something really clever when Darkhawk said
something . . .

> Darkhawk grined and said Rodimus with malice "I bet that you Girlfriend will be alone
a while..."

Rodimus looked over at Darkhawk, all the humor that had just been in
his face and voice vanishing, to be replaced by a darker more
suspicious tone, "What do you mean by that Darkhawk?"

(TAG)

Preston
